name: Future fee and charge increases or decreases
text: [§200-33]  Future fee and charge increases or decreases.  Notwithstanding section 200-32, all future fee and charge increases or decreases for vessels required to be registered and numbered pursuant to section 200-31 or for vessels owned by or operated under the custody of a boat manufacturer or boat dealer shall be established by rules adopted by the department pursuant to chapter 91.  Fees and charges established pursuant to this section shall supersede the fees and charges set forth in section 200-32. [L 1991, c 272, pt of §2]
